{
  "text": "Assume that V is a vertex operator algebra satisfying conditions (i) and (ii). The tensor product \u22a0 of V -modules was defined in a series of papers [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] and [H1] . For any V -module W , set \u03b8 W = e 2\u03c0iL(0) . Then the V -module category C V is a modular tensor category (see [H4] ).",
